{
  "texts": [
    "Cost-sensitive learning finds application in spatial modeling, scenarios involving imbalanced datasets, or situations where the impact of misclassification varies among different classes or regions.",
    "Several studies have shown it is effective in this context [84] [85] [86].",
    "Boosting Boosting algorithms are commonly used in geospatial modeling because they are superior in handling tabular spatial data and addressing class imbalance 85, 87.",
    "They effectively manage both bias and variance in ensemble models.",
    "Ensemble methods such as Bagging or Random Forest reduce variance by constructing independent decision trees, thus reducing the error that emerges from the uncertainty of a single model."
  ]
}